---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="The story behind 2nd Saturdays — a husband-and-wife ministry hosting a monthly Christian music writers round in Spring Hill, Tennessee."
>
  <section class="relative grit-dark section-paper">
    <div class="container-narrow py-16 sm:py-24 relative z-10">
      <div class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--ember-deep);">The Ministry</div>
      <h1 class="font-slab mt-5" style="font-size: clamp(3rem, 10vw, 8rem); line-height: 0.85;">
        A CIRCLE OF<br/>
        <span style="color: var(--ember-deep);">SONGWRITERS.</span><br/>
        A CIRCLE OF<br/>
        FRIENDS.
      </h1>

      <div class="mt-12 double-rule" style="color: var(--ink);"></div>

      <div class="mt-10 relative">
        <figure>
          <div
            class="relative overflow-hidden"
            style="border: 2px solid var(--ink); box-shadow: 10px 10px 0 var(--ember-deep); aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;"
          >
            <img
              src="/photos/group-large.jpg"
              alt="A community gathered after a round at Just Love Coffee Cafe."
              class="object-cover"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </div>
          <figcaption class="mt-4 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider flex items-center gap-2" style="color: var(--ink-3);">
            <span class="star" style="color: var(--ember-deep);"></span>
            The community that shows up. Spring Hill, TN.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-16 grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10">
        <div class="lg:col-span-7">
          <p class="font-serif italic leading-snug" style="font-size: 1.875rem; color: var(--ink);">
            We started 2nd Saturdays because Christian songwriters needed a
            room — and their songs needed listeners.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-8 space-y-5 leading-relaxed" style="font-size: 1.0625rem; color: var(--ink-3);">
            <p>
              We're a husband-and-wife team based in middle Tennessee. Between
              us we love good coffee, the craft of a well-written song, and
              the church.
            </p>
            <p>
              When we realized how many gifted Christian songwriters live
              within a half-hour of our front door, we wanted to give them a
              place to play their songs the way they were written — quietly,
              story-first, in front of people who came to listen.
            </p>
            <p>
              Just Love Coffee Cafe in Spring Hill said yes, and we've been
              gathering on the second Saturday of every month ever since.
              We also host a sister round, <strong>Christian Music Nights</strong>,
              in Columbia.
            </p>
            <p>
              No cover. No ticket. No fuss. Walk in, order a coffee or a meal,
              and pull up a chair. The writers are the headliners. The room
              is theirs.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lg:col-span-5">
          <div class="p-7" style="background: var(--ink); color: var(--bone); box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--ember);">
            <div class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--ember);">Sister Round</div>
            <div class="font-slab mt-3" style="font-size: 1.875rem; line-height: 0.95;">
              CHRISTIAN<br/>
              MUSIC<br/>
              <span style="color: var(--ember);">NIGHTS.</span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-4 font-serif italic leading-snug" style="font-size: 1rem; color: var(--bone-2);">
              Our second round, hosted in Columbia, TN. Same heart, different
              night.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-6 p-7" style="background: var(--ink-3); color: var(--bone); border: 2px solid var(--ink);">
            <div class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--ember);">For Songwriters</div>
            <div class="font-slab mt-3" style="font-size: 1.875rem; line-height: 0.95;">
              WANT TO<br/>
              PLAY?
            </div>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--bone-2);">
              We're always meeting new writers. Send us a note —
            </p>
            <a href="mailto:hello@2ndsaturdays.org" class="mt-3 font-mono text-sm underline-grow" style="color: var(--ember); display: inline-block;">
              hello@2ndsaturdays.org
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
